# 2. 新しいやりかた

Airi: Hmm...
Airi: I've tried adjusting our schedule a few different ways, but it just doesn't seem like we'll be able to accept more offers...
Airi: As much as I don't want to, we're gonna have to turn a few of these people down...
Airi: Hm? A new email...?
Airi: Oh, it's from that radio program. I asked them yesterday to see if they can change the meeting date, but let's see...
Airi: Not really possible, huh? I guess their producer's also pretty busy.
Airi: It would've been a nice opportunity to get our song out there, but we don't really have a choice...
Airi: Unfortunately, I'm gonna have to politely turn down their offer...
Airi: (Wait a second...)
Airi: (Shizuku and I could conceivably make it...)
Airi: (Unlike Haruka and Minori, we're credit-based, which means we don't always have to be at school.)
Airi: (But the four of us have always done everything together as MORE MORE JUMP! Would it be okay for us to go without them...?)
Airi: (I mean, it's not like we have a rule saying that we have to do absolutely everything together...)
Airi: (But I think all of us being present has made it easier to share responsibilities and move as a unit.)
Airi: (At the same time, as we keep receiving offers, we won't be able to keep doing that...)
Airi: (If we want to be given more opportunities in the future, it might be best to have even just one of us appear...)
Airi: (Which means it'd be best to take advantage of the freedom allotted to us by the credit-based course.)
Airi: But I can't make this decision on my own. We need to discuss this as a group...
Airi: Hi, Shizuku? Sorry, I know it's late. Are you free to talk right now...?
Minori: Thanks for waiting, you two!
Airi: Sorry about asking you to meet during lunch like this.
Haruka: No, that's fine... But you said there's something you wanted to talk about. Is everything okay?
Airi: Yeah, things are fine... But where do I begin?
Airi: Last night, while I was at home, I took another look at our schedule and made some adjustments. I've also already spoken to Shizuku about this.
Haruka: Adjustments to our schedule?
Airi: Yeah. We've had the fortune of receiving offers from various different people lately, right?
Airi: But we only have a finite amount of time available to us, which means we're having to turn more and more down...
Airi: So I began wondering if there's a way for us to not have to do that as much.
Minori: You've been doing all that for us, Airi...?!
Airi: It's nothing, really.
Airi: Anyway, I had an idea and talked with Shizuku about it. Would you two mind taking a look at this...?
Haruka: Our schedule...?
Minori: Huh...? Hang on... There's stuff here for weekday afternoons now.
Haruka: But it's just you and Shizuku, Airi.
Airi: Remember how we're in the credit-based course? I was hoping we could take advantage of that and adjusted our schedule accordingly.
Minori: R-Right. This would definitely allow us to accept more offers...
Minori: But...
Haruka: Yes, I do agree that we should accept whatever offers we can, even if all four of us can't be there...
Haruka: At the same time, a lot of people out there want to see us together. As such, I'd like to be careful about which offers we do accept.
Airi: I agree. This is just a preliminary idea. Just one solution for addressing how we may or may not accept more offers moving forward.
Airi: That's why I wanna hear what you think...
Haruka: How do you feel about this, Airi...?
Airi: Me...? Well...
Airi: I believe that we're gonna need to take on as many of these offers as we can if we're going to achieve our goal.
Airi: So, I think Shizuku and I should take advantage of the freedom that the credit-based course affords us.
Haruka: I see...
Haruka: Yes, you're right. I agree. However...
Haruka: I don't want to force you and Shizuku to carry a heavier burden than us.
Minori: Yeah... I'm not sure how I'd feel about you two working while we're at school...
Airi: I wouldn't worry about that. After all, this is for all of us.
Airi: I mean, being at school doesn't mean you have nothing to do, y'know...?
Minori: Huh?
Airi: There's plenty you can do here, right? For example, coming up with ideas for our stream in between classes.
Airi: If we go with this new scheduling scheme, we're gonna need you two to start handling more of those kinds of things. So, we'll be counting on you.
Minori: Oh... Y-Yeah! Okay!
Haruka: Right, we should do what we can...
Airi: Exactly. Again, we'll be counting on you.
Airi: Then, I'll start putting together a new schedule with what we just discussed in mind.
Airi: Each day's gonna start to feel a lot busier as we take on all these new offers...
Airi: But let's do our best!
